# Troitskoye, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Troitskoye () is a rural locality (a selo) in Pribaykalsky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 497 as of 2010. There are 8 streets.
Geography
Troitskoye is located 36&nbsp;km southwest of Turuntayevo (the district's administrative centre) by road. Talovka is the nearest rural locality.
